      "id": 1,
      "text": "St. James City sits on the southern half of Pine Island, with its town center at the island's southern tip.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._James_City%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The community is bordered by San Carlos Bay to the south, Pine Island Sound to the west, and Pine Island Creek to the east.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._James_City%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Stringfellow Road, also known as County Road 767, is the main north‑south artery that runs through the heart of St. James City.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
