    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1886, St. James City was incorporated just three months before Fort Myers, and the 50‑room San Carlos Hotel opened its doors in 1896.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.museumoftheislands.com/st-james-city-early-time-line/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The 50‑room San Carlos Hotel burned down in 1911 after a smudge pot was left burning, an event that marked a turning point in the town’s early tourism industry.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
